<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-21"><hi rend="italic">May 21,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>After full discussion, minister for foreign affairs declares ordinance
                            applies alike to all nationalities; that its sole motive is to sustain
                            manufactories of tobacco in Cuba, and that it is transitory. Promised
                            carefully to consider your request and to answer further after
                            conference.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>